ht|f|fp|1|cp|2|at|Showing support in a major suit:

As mentioned above, when you have a support for partner's major, you should show 
support instead of redoubling.

Most of today's players use a jump support to show a weak hand. The preempt tends to cause the opponents difficulties or even prevents them from further bidding.

But it also says that you are unable to make a jump raise with 10+ points and four card support for partner's major. How then should you show the support?

It is with a bid you don't need anymore in this kind of Auctions – the 2NT bid (with hands that naturally would bid 2NT, you now can use the redouble).|

