Now we are going to put ourselves in the opener's seat, assuming his RHO (the fourth seat) has made a bid or passed.

What should the opener do in such cases?

The answer is very simple: usually nothing!

The critical point we should remember is that the redoubler has promised a second bid and therefore the opener doesn't have to bid unless he has something very important to tell. 

From the opener's viewpoint, his partner may have something like @sKQJx in the opponents' suit and he wishes to penalise them.|
